Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.redis.client

Interface RedisSession

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    RedisClientConnection
    public interface RedisSession
    Redis session interface for sending commands.

    This interface is provided to handlers and provides methods for all common Redis operations. Commands are sent asynchronously and results are delivered via callbacks.

    Multiple commands can be issued without waiting for responses (pipelining). Redis processes commands in order and responses arrive in order.

    Author:
    Chris Burdess

      • subscribe

        void subscribe​(MessageHandler handler,
               java.lang.String... channels)
        Subscribes to channels.

        After subscribing, the connection enters Pub/Sub mode and can only execute SUBSCRIBE, PSUBSCRIBE, UNSUBSCRIBE, PUNSUBSCRIBE, PING, and QUIT.

        Parameters:
        handler - receives messages and subscription confirmations
        channels - the channels to subscribe to
